From 1f031b8189da32e17bde1c2914c530ef158b1e86 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Stefan Reinauer <stefan.reinauer@coreboot.org>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 21:46:12 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] uae: implement slirp for modern libslirp

Replace the slirp stub with a bridge for modern libslirp releases.

Create the SlirpConfig setup, callback table, timer handling, socket
notification, and QEMU main-loop integration needed to move packets
between UAE and libslirp.

Handle libslirp 4.7 and 4.9 API differences with the version checks
provided by libslirp. Keep slirp disabled in the default plugin
configure profile so qemu-uae.so does not gain the dependency unless
networking is enabled later.
---
 configure-qemu-uae   |   1 +
 uae/qemu-uae-slirp.c | 290 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---
 2 files changed, 271 insertions(+), 20 deletions(-)

